#: templates/manuals/r1.html:197
msgid "#1 Check WiFi Coverage"
msgstr "#1 检查 WiFi 覆盖范围"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                          <h5>Ensure that good 2.4GHz WiFi signal will "
"reach the device area all the time.</h5>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"alert alert-info\">\n"
"                              Optimal Wi-Fi signal strength is crucial "
"for device performance.\n"
"                              Before installation, use a mobile app (WiFi"
" Analyzer) with a 3dBm reference antenna to measure the\n"
"                              signal at the location. Ensure it's between"
" <b>-30 dBm</b> and <b>-78 dBm</b>.\n"
"                              After connecting, regularly verify this on "
"the device's webpage.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            <p class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n"
"                              If WiFi signal strength is weak consider "
"add WiFi range extenders.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h5>确保良好的 2.4GHz WiFi 信号始终到达设备区域。</h5>\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-info\" >\n"
"最佳 Wi-Fi 信号强度对于设备性能至关重要。\n"
"安装前，使用带有 3dBm 参考天线的移动应用程序（WiFi 分析仪）测量\n"
"该位置的信号。确保其介于 <b>-30 dBm</b> 和 <b>-78 dBm</b> 之间。\n"
"连接后，定期在设备网页上验证这一点。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-warning\" >\n"
"如果 WiFi 信号强度较弱，请考虑添加 WiFi 范围扩展器。\n"
"</p>\n"
"                            "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:221
msgid "#2 Pump and Safety Requirements "
msgstr "#2 泵和安全要求"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:226
msgid ""
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                              <h5>Pump Requirements</h5>\n"
"                              Ensure the pump's power consumption does "
"not exceed <b>10 amps</b> to prevent potential damage or system overload."
"\n"
"                              This translates to a maximum of <b>1200 "
"W</b> for a 120 V system and <b>2200 W</b> for a 220 V system.\n"
"                              Exceeding these limits may compromise "
"system safety and functionality.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-info\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                            <h5>Power Requirements</h5>\n"
"                            The device requires a power input of AC 120V "
"or 220V, 50/60 Hz, with a single-phase connection and neutral line.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                            <h5>Safety Requirements</h5>\n"
"                              Since this is an experimental device, the "
"user is responsible for ensuring safe installation and operation.\n"
"                              Make sure the system has a thermal breaker "
"for protection and avoid placing it near\n"
"                              flammable materials. The user should also "
"monitor the device regularly to ensure it\n"
"                              operates correctly and safely.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" role=\"alert\">\n"
"<h5>泵要求</h5>\n"
"确保泵的功耗不超过 <b>10 安培</b>，以防止潜在损坏或系统过载。\n"
"这意味着 120 V 系统的最大值为 <b>1200 W</b>，220 V 系统的最大值为 <b>2200 W</b>。\n"
"超过这些限制可能会损害系统安全性和功能。\n"
"</div>\n"
"\n"
"<div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-info\" role=\"alert\">\n"
"<h5>电源要求</h5>\n"
"该设备要求电源输入为交流 120V 或 220V、50/60 Hz、单相连接和中性线。\n"
"</div>\n"
"\n"
"<div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" role=\"alert\">\n"
"<h5>安全要求</h5>\n"
"由于这是一个实验设备，用户有责任确保安全安装和操作。\n"
"确保系统有热断路器进行保护，并避免将其放置在靠近\n"
"易燃材料。用户还应定期监控设备以确保\n"
"正确、安全地运行。\n"
"</div>\n"
"                          "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:253
msgid "#3 Installing the Controller "
msgstr "#3 安装控制器"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:263
msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h5>Device Connection Instructions</h5>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>1. Select "
"Proper Cables:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 Use cables that can handle the amperage "
"of the pump (up to 10 amps) to ensure safe operation.\n"
"                                 Make sure the cables are rated for the "
"required power load.</p>\n"
"\n"
"                              <div class=\"my-3 ms-1\"><strong>2. AC "
"Input Connections:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Identify the AC input "
"wires:</strong> You will need to identify the <strong>Line "
"(Live)</strong>, <strong>Neutral</strong>, and <strong>Ground</strong> "
"wires coming from the power source.<li>\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Connect the wires to AC-"
"IN:</strong>\n"
"                                        Connect the <strong>Line</strong>"
" (Live) wire to the <strong>Line (L)</strong> terminal,\n"
"                                        the <strong>Neutral</strong> wire"
" to the <strong>Neutral (N)</strong> terminal, and the "
"<strong>Ground</strong> wire to the\n"
"                                       <strong>Ground (G)</strong> "
"terminal on the device's <strong>AC-IN</strong> section. Make sure each "
"wire is properly secured\n"
"                                       to avoid any loose connections.\n"
"                                     </li>\n"
"                                 </ul>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                              <div class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>3. AC "
"Output Connections:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Connect to the "
"pump:</strong> In the <strong>AC-Out</strong> section of the device, "
"repeat the process\n"
"                                       by connecting the "
"<strong>Line</strong> wire to the <strong>Line (L)</strong> terminal,\n"
"                                       the <strong>Neutral</strong> wire "
"to the <strong>Neutral (N)</strong> terminal,\n"
"                                       and the <strong>Ground</strong> "
"wire to the <strong>Ground (G)</strong> terminal.<li>\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       Make sure the connections are "
"correct, secure, and tight to ensure reliable operation of the pump.<li>"
"\n"
"                                 </ul>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>4. Mount the "
"Device:</strong><br>\n"
"                              Use the <strong>mount points</strong> on "
"the device to securely attach it to a wall\n"
"                              or other stable surface. Ensure the "
"mounting location is dry, accessible, and allows for proper ventilation "
"around the device.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>5. Verify "
"Connections:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 Before turning the device on, double-"
"check all connections to ensure they are correctly placed and there are "
"no errors. Incorrect wiring could lead to malfunctions or damage to the "
"pump.</p>\n"
"                           "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h5>设备连接说明</h5>\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>1。选择合适的电缆：</strong><br>\n"
"使用能够承受泵电流强度（高达 10 安培）的电缆，以确保安全运行。\n"
"确保电缆额定功率满足所需的功率负载。</p>\n"
"\n"
"<div class=\"my-3 ms-1\" ><strong>2。交流输入连接：</strong><br>\n"
"<ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-item-"
"primary\" >\n"
"<strong>识别交流输入线：</strong> 您需要识别来自电源的 "
"<strong>Line（Live）</strong>、<strong>Neutral</strong> 和 "
"<strong>Ground</strong> 线。</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-item-"
"primary\" >\n"
"<strong>将电线连接到交流输入：</strong>\n"
"将 <strong>Line</strong>（火线）线连接到 <strong>Line (L)</strong> 端子，\n"
"将 <strong>Neutral</strong> 线连接到 <strong>Neutral (N)</strong> 端子，并将 "
"<strong>Ground</strong> 线连接到\n"
"设备 <strong>AC-IN</strong> 部分上的 <strong> 接地 (G)</strong> 端子。确保每根电线均已正确固定\n"
"以避免任何松动的连接。\n"
"</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"</div>\n"
"\n"
"<div class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>3。交流输出连接：</strong><br>\n"
"<ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-item-"
"primary\">\n"
"<strong>连接到泵：</strong> 在设备的 <strong>AC-Out</strong> 部分，重复该过程\n"
"将 <strong>Line</strong> 电线连接到 <strong>Line (L)</strong> 端子，\n"
"将 <strong>Neutral</strong> 电线连接到 <strong>Neutral (N)</strong> 端子，\n"
"和 <strong>Ground</strong> 电线到 <strong>Ground (G)</strong> 端子。</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-item-"
"primary\">\n"
"确保连接正确、牢固且紧密，以确保泵可靠运行。</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"</div>\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>4。安装设备：</strong><br>\n"
"使用设备上的 <strong> 安装点 </strong> 将其牢固地固定在墙上\n"
"或其他稳定的表面。确保安装位置干燥、易于接近，并且设备周围通风良好。\n"
"</p>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>5。验证连接：</strong><br>\n"
"在打开设备之前，请仔细检查所有连接以确保它们正确放置并且没有错误。接线错误可能会导致泵故障或损坏。</p>\n"
"                           "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:312
msgid "#4 Configure Wi-Fi connection for the device. "
msgstr "#4 配置设备的 Wi-Fi 连接。"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:317
msgid ""
"\n"
"                          <p>In this step, configure the device to "
"connect to your local internet WiFi network</p>\n"
"                          <div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n"
"                            To enjoy all the features of this device, "
"you'll need to <a href=\"/register\" target=\"_blank\">create a free "
"account</a>\n"
"                            using your email address. <br>\n"
"                            This will allow you to link the device to "
"your profile\n"
"                            and personalize your settings.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          <h5>Steps:</h5>\n"
"                          <ul class=\"list-group ms-1\">\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                                <b>1)</b> Connect the device to an AC "
"power source and switch the <a href=\"#collapsePartOne\"><b>Manual/Smart "
"Switch</b></a>\n"
"                                to the <b>ON</b> position. This will "
"power on the LEDs and screen, enabling the smart features\n"
"                                of the pump controller. Ensure the WiFi "
"antenna is securely connected to the <b>Pump Controller</b>.\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>2)</b> Using a cellphone, search and "
"connect to a 2.4GHz WiFi network named <b>WaterLevelProSetup</b> with "
"credentials/password: <b>1122334455</b>\n"
"                              <div class=\"alert alert-warning mt-2\">\n"
"                                If the network name doesn't show or "
"disappears quickly, check <b>AC</b> power input or press the WiFi Reset "
"button at <b>Pump Controller</b>.\n"
"                                <div class=\"alert alert-info mt-3\">\n"
"                                  To reset the WiFi, press the <b>WiFi "
"Reset</b> button 5 consecutive times.\n"
"                                </div>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>3) Enter your local WiFi auth info.</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                After completing step <b>2)</b>, a "
"Captive Portal will appear on your cellphone. This will guide you to a "
"webpage where\n"
"                                you can select the desired Wi-Fi network "
"and enter its credentials. You will also be prompted to enter an\n"
"                                email address to link the device to your "
"existing account.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                If the Captive Portal don't load "
"automatically use this url\n"
"                                <a href=\"http://192.168.4.1/\" "
"target=\"_blank\">http://192.168.4.1/</a> to load it manually from "
"cellphone.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>4) Check your device is online</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                Reconnect your cellphone to the internet "
"and log in to your account. If everything\n"
"                                  was successful, after <b>2 minute</b>, "
"you will see the new device listed in your account with an "
"<b>\"Online\"</b> status.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                If the device does not show online after "
"<b>2 minute</b>, try reconnecting the power source or repeating\n"
"                                the entire process after pressing the "
"<b>WiFi Reset</b> button 5 consecutive times on the device.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                          </ul>\n"
"                          "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<p>在此步骤中，配置设备以连接到本地互联网 WiFi 网络</p>\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-info\" >\n"
"要享受此设备的所有功能，您需要<a href=\"/register\" target=\"_blank\" >创建一个免费帐户</a>\n"
"使用您的电子邮件地址。 <br>\n"
"这将允许您将设备链接到您的个人资料\n"
"并个性化您的设置。\n"
"</div>\n"
"<h5>步骤：</h5>\n"
"<ul class=\"list-group ms-1\" >\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\">\n"
"<b>1)</b> 将设备连接到交流电源并切换 <a href=\"#collapsePartOne\" ><b>手动/智能开关</b></a>\n"
"到 <b>ON</b> 位置。这将为 LED 和屏幕供电，从而启用智能功能\n"
"泵控制器。确保 WiFi 天线牢固连接到 <b> 泵控制器 </b>。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"<b>2)</b> 使用手机搜索并连接到名为 <b>WaterLevelProSetup</b> 的 2.4GHz WiFi "
"网络，凭据/密码为：<b>1122334455</b>\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-warning mt-2\">\n"
"如果网络名称未显示或快速消失，请检查 <b>AC</b> 电源输入或按 <b>Pump Controller</b> 处的 WiFi 重置按钮。\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-info mt-3\" >\n"
"要重置 WiFi，请连续按 <b>WiFi Reset</b> 按钮 5 次。\n"
"</div>\n"
"</div>\n"
"\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"<b>3) 输入您本地的 WiFi 身份验证信息.</b>\n"
"<p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"完成步骤 <b>2)</b> 后，您的手机上将出现强制门户。这将引导您进入一个网页，其中\n"
"您可以选择所需的 Wi-Fi 网络并输入其凭据。系统还会提示您输入\n"
"用于将设备链接到您现有帐户的电子邮件地址。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"如果 Captive Portal 未自动加载，请使用此 url\n"
"<a href=\"http://192.168.4.1/\" target=\"_blank\">http://192.168.4.1/</a>"
" 从手机手动加载。\n"
"</p>\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\">\n"
"<b>4) 检查您的设备是否在线</b>\n"
"<p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"将手机重新连接到互联网并登录您的 <b>Waterlevel.Pro</b> 帐户。如果一切\n"
"成功，<b>2 分钟</b> 后，您将看到帐户中列出的新设备，状态为 <b>\"在线\"</b>。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"如果 <b>2 分钟</b> 后设备未显示在线，请尝试重新连接电源或重复\n"
"连续按设备上的 <b>WiFi Reset</b> 按钮 5 次后的整个过程。\n"
"</p>\n"
"</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"                          "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:374
msgid "#5 Smart Settings "
msgstr "#5 智能设置"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:427
msgid "#6 Manual Mode - <b> Manual/Smart Switch</b> "
msgstr "#6 手动模式 - <b> 手动/智能开关</b>"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:432
msgid ""
"\n"
"                            <h5>Using the <b>Manual/Smart Switch</b> "
"Button</h5>\n"
"                            <p class=\"ms-2 my-3\">\n"
"                                The physical <a "
"href=\"#collapsePartOne\"><b>Manual/Smart Switch</b></a> button on\n"
"                                the pump controller allows you to operate"
" the pump manually, functioning like a simple\n"
"                                switch that turns the pump on without "
"requiring internet or smart features. To enable this,\n"
"                                move the <a "
"href=\"#collapsePartOne\"><b>Manual/Smart Switch</b></a> to the OFF "
"position.\n"
"                                The LEDs and screen will turn off, but "
"the pump will start running.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            <div class=\"alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                                Before switching to <b>Manual Mode</b>, "
"verify that the pump is not <b>ON</b> while in <b>Smart Mode</b>.\n"
"                                Use the web UI control to check its "
"status. Confirm that the green indicator <b>LED</b> is off before "
"proceeding.\n"
"                            </div>\n"
"                            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h5>使用<b>手动/智能开关</b>按钮</h5>\n"
"<p class=\"ms-2 my-3\" >\n"
"物理 <a href=\"#collapsePartOne\" ><b> 手动/智能开关 </b></a> 按钮\n"
"泵控制器允许您手动操作泵，其功能就像一个简单的\n"
"无需互联网或智能功能即可打开泵的开关。为了实现这一点，\n"
"将<a href=\"#collapsePartOne\" ><b>手动/智能开关</b></a>移至关闭位置。\n"
"LED 和屏幕将关闭，但泵将开始运行。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-danger\" role=\"alert\" >\n"
"在切换到 <b> 手动模式 </b> 之前，请验证泵在 <b> 智能模式 </b> 下时是否处于 <b>ON</b> 状态。\n"
"使用 Web UI 控件检查其状态。继续操作前请确认绿色指示灯 <b>LED</b> 已关闭。\n"
"</div>\n"
"                            "

