msgstr "控制单元"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:42
msgid "Contains WiFi antenna, setup/reset button, and power inputs."
msgstr "包含 WiFi 天线、设置/重置按键及电源输入。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:46 templates/manuals/s1.html:181
msgid "Internal Water Tank Sensor"
msgstr "内部水箱传感器"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:47
msgid "Measures water level and must be placed inside the water tank."
msgstr "用于测量水位，必须安装在水箱内部。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:51
msgid "Installation Steps"
msgstr "安装步骤"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:52
msgid ""
"Includes WiFi coverage check, power supply options, and setup "
"instructions."
msgstr "包括 WiFi 覆盖检查、电源选项与配置说明。"

msgid ""
"\n"
"      The <b>WiFi Water Level S1</b> device connects to your Wi-Fi "
"network and enables remote water level monitoring via the\n"
"      this web platform. It also integrates with the"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<b>WiFi Water Level S1</b> 设备可连接到您的 Wi-Fi 网络，并通过\n"
"WaterLevel.Pro 平台实现远程水位监测。它还可与以下设备联动："

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:137
msgid ""
"allowing automatic control of water pumps based on the water level "
"readings. An internet connection is required for\n"
"      cloud synchronization, enabling real-time tracking and control."
msgstr ""
"可根据水位读数自动控制水泵。系统需要联网以进行\n"
"云端同步，从而实现实时监测与远程控制。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:167
msgid ""
"The <strong>Control Unit</strong> is placed on the outside of the water "
"tank."
msgstr "<strong>控制单元</strong>放置在水箱的外部。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:187
msgid " Use any from <b>HCSR04</b> sensors family, that can work with <b>3.3V</b>"
msgstr "可使用 <b>HCSR04</b> 系列中支持 <b>3.3V</b> 的传感器。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:191
msgid "recommended"
msgstr "推荐"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:194
msgid "could require special case and waterproof treatment"
msgstr "可能需要专用外壳与防水处理"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:246
msgid "Check WiFi Coverage"
msgstr "检查 WiFi 覆盖范围"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:270
msgid "Choose Power Supply"
msgstr "选择电源"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:275
msgid "Input Power Options:"
msgstr "输入电源选项："

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:280
msgid "Solar Panel Lid"
msgstr "太阳能电池板盖"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:283
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                In locations receiving direct sunlight "
"for at least 3 hours per day, the solar\n"
"                                panel lid can be utilized.\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"在每天接受阳光直射至少 3 小时的地方，太阳能\n"
"可以使用面板盖。\n"
"                                "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                 <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                   Completely wireless and capable of "
"operating autonomously through solar power,\n"
"                                   provided the area receives sufficient "
"sunlight.\n"
"                                 </li>\n"
"                                 <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                   Designed and tested for outdoor use, "
"resistant to rain, sunlight, and typical outdoor weather conditions.\n"
"                                 </li>\n"
"                                 <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                     Powered by 3 AA NiMH rechargeable "
"batteries, the device offers easy maintenance\n"
"                                      and provides backup power during "
"periods of low sunlight.\n"
"                                 </li>\n"
"                                 <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                   Ensure use good brand and quality AA "
"NiMH batteries, 2000 mA or more.\n"
"                                 </li>\n"
"                                 <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action list-group-item-danger\">\n"
"                                    Only use AA NiMH rechargeable "
"batteries.\n"
"                                 </li>\n"
"                                 <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action list-group-item-danger\">\n"
"                                   To prevent damage to the device, "
"please remove batteries if they are depleted, damaged, or\n"
"                                     if the device will be stored for an "
"extended period without exposure to sunlight.\n"
"                                 </li>\n"
"                                 "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"完全无线并能够通过太阳能自主运行，\n"
"只要该区域有足够的阳光。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"专为户外使用而设计和测试，耐雨水、阳光和典型的户外天气条件。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"该设备由 3 节 AA NiMH 可充电电池供电，维护方便\n"
"并在阳光不足时提供备用电源。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"确保使用品牌优质 AA 镍氢电池，2000 mA 或以上。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-item-"
"danger\" >\n"
"仅使用 AA NiMH 可充电电池。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-item-"
"danger\" >\n"
"为防止损坏设备，如果电池电量耗尽、损坏或耗尽，请取出电池\n"
"如果设备将长期存放而不暴露在阳光下。\n"
"</li>\n"
"                                 "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:313
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                   When using solar power as the input, "
"ensure the <b>USB-C</b> port is sealed to\n"
"                                   prevent damage from rain or moisture. "
"Use the provided <b>USB-C cap</b> and optionally\n"
"                                   seal it with silicone for added "
"protection.\n"
"                                   "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"当使用太阳能作为输入时，确保 <b>USB-C</b> 端口密封以\n"
"防止雨水或湿气造成损坏。使用提供的 <b>USB-C cap</b> 并可选\n"
"用硅胶密封它以提供额外的保护。\n"
"                                   "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:330
msgid "USBC Power"
msgstr "USB-C 供电"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h6 class=\"ms-1 my-2\">\n"
"                                To operate in indoor environments or "
"areas with limited sunlight, simply connect the device to a power source "
"using the <b>USB-C</b> port.\n"
"                              </h6>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"ms-1 alert alert-warning\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                                <b>Note:</b> When using the USB-C port "
"for power, please ensure that batteries are removed to prevent damage to "
"the device.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"ms-1 alert alert-warning\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                                <b>Note:</b> Using the AC/DC power "
"adapter outdoors or near water requires special safety\n"
"                                precautions. Consult a qualified "
"electrician if necessary. Ensure all cables are\n"
"                                properly insulated to protect them from "
"water and unpredictable weather conditions.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <p class=\"ms-1\">\n"
"                                Depending on the water level measurement "
"frequency configured for the device, it could consume up to\n"
"                                70 mA for approximately 6 seconds at "
"3.3V, each cycle.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <p class=\"ms-1 alert alert-info\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                                <b>Power Selection:</b>\n"
"                                To select your preferred power source "
"(Solar, USB-C), locate the <a href=\"#power_control\">Power Selector</a> "
"switch\n"
"                                on the device. Toggle the switch to the "
"desired setting.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h6 class=\"ms-1 my-2\" >\n"
"要在室内环境或阳光有限的区域中运行，只需使用 <b>USB-C</b> 端口将设备连接到电源即可。\n"
"</h6>\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"ms-1 alert alert-warning\" role=\"alert\"  >\n"
"<b>注意：</b> 使用 USB-C 端口供电时，请确保取出电池，以免损坏设备。\n"
"</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"ms-1 alert alert-warning\" role=\"alert\" >\n"
"<b>注意：</b> 在户外或靠近水的地方使用 AC/DC 电源适配器需要特别安全\n"
"防范措施。如有必要，请咨询合格的电工。确保所有电缆均已\n"
"适当绝缘，以保护它们免受水和不可预测的天气条件的影响。\n"
"</p>\n"
"\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"<p class=\"ms-1\" >\n"
"根据为设备配置的水位测量频率，它可能消耗最多\n"
"每个周期在 3.3V 下电流为 70 mA，持续约 6 秒。\n"
"</p>\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"<p class=\"ms-1 alert alert-info\" role=\"alert\"   >\n"
"<b>电源选择：</b>\n"
"要选择您的首选电源（太阳能、USB-C），请找到 <a href=\"#power_control\" >电源选择器</a> 开关\n"
"在设备上。将开关切换到所需的设置。\n"
"</p>\n"
"</li>\n"
"                            "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                      <h2 class=\"accordion-header\" id=\"headingThree\">"
"\n"
"                        <button class=\"accordion-button collapsed\" "
"type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-"
"target=\"#collapseThree\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-"
"controls=\"collapseThree\">\n"
"                         #3 Configure Wi-Fi connection for the device.\n"
"                        </button>\n"
"                      </h2>\n"
"                      <div id=\"collapseThree\" class=\"accordion-"
"collapse collapse\" aria-labelledby=\"headingThree\">\n"
"                        <div class=\"accordion-body\">\n"
"                          <p>In this step, configure the device to "
"connect to your local internet WiFi network</p>\n"
"                          <div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n"
"                            To enjoy all the features of this device, "
"you'll need to <a href=\"/register\" target=\"_blank\">create a free "
"account</a>\n"
"                            using your email address. <br>\n"
"                            This will allow you to link the device to "
"your profile\n"
"                            and personalize your settings.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          <h5>Steps:</h5>\n"
"                          <ul class=\"list-group ms-1\">\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>1)</b> Connect the device to a power "
"source. Ensure WiFi antenna is connected at <b>Control Unit</b>.\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>2)</b> Using a cellphone, search and "
"connect to a 2.4GHz WiFi network named <b>WaterLevelProSetup</b> with "
"credentials/password: <b>1122334455</b>\n"
"                              <div class=\"alert alert-warning mt-2\">\n"
"                                If the network name doesn't show or "
"disappears quickly, check <b>USBC</b> power input or press the WiFi Reset"
" button at <b>Control Unit</b>.\n"
"                                <div class=\"alert alert-info mt-3\">\n"
"                                  To reset the Wi-Fi, power on the device"
" using either the <b>USBC</b> cable or solar power.\n"
"                                  Immediately after powering on, quickly "
"press the Wi-Fi Reset button 2-3 times.\n"
"                                </div>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>3) Enter your local WiFi auth info.</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                After completing step <b>2)</b>, a "
"Captive Portal will appear on your cellphone. This will guide you to a "
"webpage where\n"
"                                you can select the desired Wi-Fi network "
"and enter its credentials. You will also be prompted to enter an\n"
"                                email address to link the device to your "
"existing account.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                If the Captive Portal don't load "
"automatically use this url\n"
"                                <a href=\"http://192.168.4.1/\" "
"target=\"_blank\">http://192.168.4.1/</a> to load it manually from "
"cellphone.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>4) Check your device is online</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                Reconnect your cellphone to the internet "
"and log in to your account. If everything\n"
"                                was successful, you will see the new "
"device listed in your account with an <b>\"Online\"</b> status.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                If the device does not show online, try "
"reconnecting the power source or repeating\n"
"                                the entire process after pressing the <b"
">Wi-Fi Reset</b> button on the device.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                          </ul>\n"
"                        </div>\n"
"                      </div>\n"
"                      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h2 class=\"accordion-header\" id=\"headingThree\">\n"
"<button class=\"accordion-button collapsed\" type=\"button\" data-bs-"
"toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#collapseThree\" aria-"
"expanded=\"false\" aria-controls=\"collapseThree\">\n"
"#3 配置设备的 Wi-Fi 连接。\n"
"</button>\n"
"</h2>\n"
"<div id=\"collapseThree\" class=\"accordion-collapse collapse\" aria-"
"labelledby=\"headingThree\" >\n"
"<div class=\"accordion-body\">\n"
"<p>在此步骤中，配置设备以连接到本地互联网 WiFi 网络</p>\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-info\" >\n"
"要享受此设备的所有功能，您需要<a href=\"/register\" target=\"_blank\" >创建一个免费帐户</a>\n"
"使用您的电子邮件地址。 <br>\n"
"这将允许您将设备链接到您的个人资料\n"
"并个性化您的设置。\n"
"</div>\n"
"<h5>步骤：</h5>\n"
"<ul class=\"list-group ms-1\" >\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\">\n"
"<b>1)</b> 将设备连接至电源。确保 WiFi 天线已连接至 <b>控制单元</b>。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"<b>2)</b> 使用手机搜索并连接到名为 <b>WaterLevelProSetup</b> 的 2.4GHz WiFi "
"网络，凭据/密码为：<b>1122334455</b>\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-warning mt-2\">\n"
"如果网络名称未显示或快速消失，请检查<b>USBC</b>电源输入或按<b>控制单元</b>上的WiFi重置按钮。\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-info mt-3\" >\n"
"要重置 Wi-Fi，请使用 <b>USBC</b> 电缆或太阳能打开设备电源。\n"
"开机后立即快速按 Wi-Fi 重置按钮 2-3 次。\n"
"</div>\n"
"</div>\n"
"\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"<b>3) 输入您本地的 WiFi 身份验证信息.</b>\n"
"<p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"完成步骤 <b>2)</b> 后，您的手机上将出现强制门户。这将引导您进入一个网页，其中\n"
"您可以选择所需的 Wi-Fi 网络并输入其凭据。系统还会提示您输入\n"
"用于将设备链接到您现有帐户的电子邮件地址。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"如果 Captive Portal 未自动加载，请使用此 url\n"
"<a href=\"http://192.168.4.1/\" target=\"_blank\">http://192.168.4.1/</a>"
" 从手机手动加载。\n"
"</p>\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\">\n"
"<b>4) 检查您的设备是否在线</b>\n"
"<p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"将手机重新连接到互联网并登录您的 <b>Waterlevel.Pro</b> 帐户。如果一切\n"
"成功后，您将看到您的帐户中列出了新设备，其状态为 <b>\"在线\"</b>。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"如果设备未显示在线，请尝试重新连接电源或重复\n"
"按下设备上的 <b>Wi-Fi Reset</b> 按钮后的整个过程。\n"
"</p>\n"
"</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"</div>\n"
"</div>\n"
"                      "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:431
msgid "Placing the device on the water tank."
msgstr "将设备放置在水箱上。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:439
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                Place the device sensor as far as "
"possible from the main water inlet of the water tank,\n"
"                                without reaching to much closer to the "
"water tank internal wall, to avoid erroneous\n"
"                                measurements when filling the water tank."
"\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"将设备传感器放置在距离水箱主进水口尽可能远的地方，\n"
"无需将手伸得太靠近水箱内壁，以避免错误\n"
"给水箱注水时的测量。\n"
"                                "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:457
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                  Keep in mind that the internal sensor "
"that is placed inside the water tank must have a minimum margin of <b>20 "
"centimeters (AJ-SR04M Sensor)</b>\n"
"                                  from its bottom location to the maximum"
" distance that the water in the tank can reach.\n"
"                                  "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"请记住，放置在水箱内的内部传感器必须具有 <b>20 厘米的最小边距（AJ-SR04M 传感器）</b>\n"
"从其底部位置到水箱中的水可以到达的最大距离。\n"
"                                  "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                <p class=\"alert alert-danger my-2\">\n"
"                                   If the tank cannot preserve that "
"minimum distance margin, the sensor blind area is\n"
"                                  reached and erroneous random "
"measurements will be reported.\n"
"                                  Use the <b>RCWL-1670 Sensor</b> if "
"require smaller blind area (2 CM).\n"
"                                </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                The installation location may vary "
"depending on the shape of your water tank, how\n"
"                                the lid closes, and its resistance to "
"local conditions. Please choose an installation\n"
"                                method that ensures the device is "
"securely mounted and protected. As this is an experimental device,\n"
"                                the user is responsible for ensuring "
"proper and safe installation.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-danger my-2\" >\n"
"如果储罐无法保持最小距离裕度，则传感器盲区为\n"
"将报告达到的和错误的随机测量值。\n"
"如果需要较小的盲区 (2 CM)，请使用 <b>RCWL-1670 传感器</b>。\n"
"</p>\n"
"<p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\" >\n"
"安装位置可能会有所不同，具体取决于水箱的形状、方式\n"
"盖子关闭，及其对当地条件的抵抗力。请选择安装\n"
"确保设备牢固安装和保护的方法。由于这是一个实验装置，\n"
"用户有责任确保正确和安全的安装。\n"
"</p>\n"
"                              "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h4>Placement of the upper Control "
"Unit.</h4>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-3\">\n"
"                                The control unit can be installed using "
"two main methods, depending on your\n"
"                                specific setup and preferences. Please "
"ensure that the chosen method provides a\n"
"                                secure and stable mounting for optimal "
"performance.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"\n"
"                              <h5>Screw Mounting Method: </h5>\n"
"                              "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h4>上部控制单元的放置.</h4>\n"
"\n"
"<p class=\"my-3\" >\n"
"控制单元可以使用两种主要方法安装，具体取决于您的\n"
"具体设置和偏好。请确保所选方法提供\n"
"安全稳定的安装以获得最佳性能。\n"
"</p>\n"
"\n"
"<h5>螺钉安装方法：</h5>\n"
"                              "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Locate the designated mounting points "
"on the control unit.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Use appropriate screws to securely "
"fasten the unit to a flat surface, such as a wall or a sturdy panel near "
"the water tank.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Ensure the screws are tight and the "
"unit is firmly fixed to avoid movement or detachment over time.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"找到控制单元上指定的安装点。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"使用适当的螺钉将设备牢固地固定在平坦表面上，例如墙壁或水箱附近的坚固面板。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\">\n"
"确保螺钉拧紧并且装置牢固固定，以避免随着时间的推移而移动或分离。\n"
"</li>\n"
"                                "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:512
msgid "Pipe Mounting Method:"
msgstr "管道安装方法："

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:520
msgid ""
"This method is ideal for installations over a pipe or cylindrical "
"structure with a diameter of approximately 27mm."
msgstr "此方法非常适合安装在直径约为 27 毫米的管道或圆柱形结构上。"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Use the screws, nuts, and mounting "
"accessories provided with the model to securely\n"
"                                  attach the control unit to a pipe of "
"approximately 27mm in diameter.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Ensure the unit is tightly secured and "
"aligned properly to prevent shifting or tilting during operation.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  For the pipe mounting option, inspect "
"the quality of the 3D-printed screws, as they\n"
"                                  may break depending on the print "
"quality, material, or other factors.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"使用随型号提供的螺钉、螺母和安装附件将其牢固地固定\n"
"将控制单元连接到直径约 27mm 的管道上。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\">\n"
"确保设备牢固固定并正确对齐，以防止操作过程中移动或倾斜。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" >\n"
"对于管道安装选项，请检查 3D 打印螺钉的质量，因为它们\n"
"根据打印质量、材料或其他因素，可能会破裂。\n"
"</li>\n"
"                                "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:544
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                Regardless of the installation method, "
"always verify that the control unit is\n"
"                                mounted in a location that is safe, "
"stable, and well-protected from adverse\n"
"                                environmental conditions.\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"无论采用何种安装方法，请务必验证控制单元是否正常\n"
"安装在安全、稳定且免受不利影响的位置\n"
"环境条件。\n"
"                                "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h4>Positioning the Control Unit for Solar "
"Power</h4>\n"
"                              <p>\n"
"                                If you are using solar power to operate "
"the control unit, it is crucial to position\n"
"                                the device to maximize its exposure to "
"sunlight. Follow these guidelines for\n"
"                                optimal solar performance:\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 list-group-"
"numbered\">\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Orientation:</b> Ensure the solar panel is facing the "
"direction that receives the most\n"
"                                  sunlight during the day. In most "
"regions, this means orienting the panel toward\n"
"                                  the south in the northern hemisphere or"
" toward the north in the southern hemisphere.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Avoid Obstructions: </b>  Place the control unit in an "
"area free from shadows\n"
"                                  caused by trees, buildings, or other "
"objects that could block sunlight during the day.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Regular Maintenance: </b>\n"
"                                  Clean the solar panel periodically with"
" mild soap and water,\n"
"                                  avoiding alcohol or harsh chemicals. "
"Use a soft cloth and rinse thoroughly to remove\n"
"                                  any soap residue, ensuring the panel "
"stays efficient and protected.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                              </ul>\n"
"                              "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<h4>定位太阳能控制单元</h4>\n"
"<p>\n"
"如果您使用太阳能来操作控制单元，则定位至关重要\n"
"该设备最大限度地暴露在阳光下。请遵循以下指南\n"
"最佳太阳能性能：\n"
"</p>\n"
"<ul class=\"list-group ms-1 list-group-numbered\" >\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\"><b>方向：</b> "
"确保太阳能电池板面向接收最多的方向\n"
"白天的阳光。在大多数地区，这意味着将面板朝向\n"
"北半球朝南或南半球朝北。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" ><b>避免障碍物：</b> "
"将控制单元放置在没有阴影的区域\n"
"由树木、建筑物或其他可能在白天阻挡阳光的物体引起。\n"
"</li>\n"
"<li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action\" ><b>定期维护：</b>\n"
"定期用温和的肥皂和水清洁太阳能电池板，\n"
"避免酒精或刺激性化学物质。使用软布彻底冲洗以去除\n"
"任何肥皂残留物，确保面板保持高效并受到保护。\n"
"</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"                              "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:576
msgid "Mount the AJ-SR04M Internal Sensor"
msgstr "安装 AJ-SR04M 内部传感器"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:587
msgid "Drill a 12mm hole in the tank lid, far from the water inlet and wall."
msgstr "在水箱盖上钻一个 12 毫米的孔，远离进水口和墙壁。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:590
msgid "Thread the sensor cable through, pointing the sensor toward the water."
msgstr "将传感器电缆穿过，将传感器指向水。"

