#: templates/manuals/s1.html:655
msgid "Adjust Device Settings"
msgstr "调整设备设置"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:660
msgid "To accurately measure the water level in the tank, you need to set the device to recognize the point where the tank is considered empty. In summary, this ensures the device calculates the tank's total capacity correctly."
msgstr "要准确测量水箱中的水位，您需要将设备设置为识别水箱被视为空的点。总之，这可确保设备正确计算水箱总容量。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:664
msgid "2) Update the \"Empty Level\" in Settings"
msgstr "2) 在设置中更新\"空水位\""

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:670
msgid "In the settings, adjust the <b>\"Empty Level\"</b> by entering the distance (in centimeters) from the internal sensor to the bottom of the tank, representing the point at which you consider the tank to be empty."
msgstr "在设置中，通过输入内部传感器到底部的距离（厘米）来调整 <b>\"空水位\"</b>，该值表示您认为水箱为空的点。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:675
msgid "3) Update the \"Top Margin\" in Settings"
msgstr "3) 在设置中更新\"顶部边距\""

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:677
msgid "The <b>Top Margin</b> property specifies the unused space at the top of the water tank. Typically, tanks have at least 20 cm of empty space at the top to prevent overflows, controlled by a float valve or similar mechanism. Setting this value ensures more accurate readings, indicating when the tank is truly at 100&#37; capacity."
msgstr "<b>顶部边距</b> 属性用于定义水箱顶部未使用空间。通常，水箱顶部至少保留 20 厘米空隙以防溢出，该空间由浮球阀或类似机制控制。设置该值可提升读数准确性，并指示水箱何时真正达到 100&#37; 容量。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:680
msgid "In the settings, adjust the <b>Top Margin</b> to define the distance (in centimeters) from the sensor to the maximum water level. This ensures the system accounts for the unused space at the top of the tank, providing more accurate measurements of full capacity."
msgstr "在设置中，调整 <b>顶部边距</b> 以定义传感器到最高水位的距离（厘米）。这可确保系统考虑水箱顶部未使用空间，从而提供更准确的满容量测量。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:684
msgid "Depending on the sensor model, it may have a blind spot where it cannot detect accurately. If the water level enters this blind area, the sensor might report random or unreliable measurements."
msgstr "根据传感器型号不同，可能存在无法准确检测的盲区。如果水位进入该盲区，传感器可能会报告随机或不可靠的测量值。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:687
msgid "The <b>AJ-SR04M</b> sensor has a blind area of <b>20 cm</b>, meaning it cannot measure distances within this range. To ensure accurate readings, a Top Margin of at least 20 cm is required."
msgstr "<b>AJ-SR04M</b> 传感器的盲区为 <b>20 厘米</b>，即该范围内无法测距。为确保读数准确，顶部边距至少需设置为 20 厘米。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:692
msgid "The <b>RCWL-1670</b> sensor has a blind area of <b>2 cm</b>, meaning it cannot measure accurately within this range. To ensure proper functionality, set a Top Margin of at least 2 cm."
msgstr "<b>RCWL-1670</b> 传感器的盲区为 <b>2 厘米</b>，即该范围内无法精确测距。为确保功能正常，请将顶部边距至少设置为 2 厘米。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:698
msgid "4) Update \"Liters per cm\" in Settings"
msgstr "4) 在设置中更新\"每厘米升数\""

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:700
msgid "Set <b>Liters per cm</b> to convert each centimeter of water height into liters. This helps the app show volume changes more accurately."
msgstr "设置 <b>每厘米升数</b>，将每 1 厘米水位高度转换为升数。这有助于应用更准确地显示容量变化。"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:703
msgid "Quick estimate: <b>Liters per cm = usable tank liters / usable tank height in cm</b>. Start with this value and fine-tune after a few real fill/drain cycles."
msgstr "快速估算：<b>每厘米升数 = 水箱可用升数 / 水箱可用高度（厘米）</b>。先用该值，经过几次真实的注水/放水循环后再微调。"

